<sect1 id="dir_d7d61354c43df5b3f9e499bdacf27dcd_1autotoc_md215">
<title>Key Concepts</title><para><bold>GameWorld</bold> owns all GameObjects and provides query methods for component-based iteration. It manages the lifecycle of entities and coordinates with pools and managers.</para>
<para><bold>GameLoop</bold> orchestrates the frame update cycle through three phases (Pre, Main, Post), each containing passes that execute systems in order.</para>
<para><bold>CommandBuffer</bold> collects commands during a phase and flushes them to dispatchers after each phase completes.</para>
<para><bold>GameLoopEventBus</bold> manages phase-level and pass-level event propagation using a double-buffer pattern.</para>
